        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What’s it mean to go to a top school? Or a private one?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "What’s it for?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Does it inherently make someone smarter or more able?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or is it a gimmick? A false pretense? Or, an arbitrary qualifier?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "If you’re willing to give them a chance, you’ll find that people from less than stellar backgrounds are often just as, if not more, capable than those who are.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "A diploma from an elite school is a vanity metric. One that’s often not entirely based on merit.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s mainly a signal of status, privilege, and luck.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}